phrases: There are so many people at Yunosagi!
People also visit from outside the prefecture.
Is not it a little too early to give up?
FM: Ko Sub: (non title) in Yunosagi just now.
Sorry, I need to go pick up Ko!
Go and fest it up without me!
She is a noisy one, as usual.
Is it okay to let her go?
I do not see why not.
What did you write on it?
I want to become a bullet train!
What do I want to become?
I may not act like it, but I am actually pretty pragmatic.
I do not live with the greatest role model.
Hey, do you think this is fine?
Did not I say that we can say anything to each other?
Hey, Mom, will you buy me a caramel apple?
You mean, Ohana is just like me.
You should not look at other people's wishes.
I want to be Sui Shijima -Ohana.
I want to be like the Madam Manager,
who takes pride in her job and works her hardest,
but is a little childish and never forgets her first wish -
But I could not find that goal on my own.
Everyone is bonboris lit my way toward it.
But that just means I need to fest it up.
Have not you heard Ohana use it?
I hope to catch up to Tohru someday -Minko I would like to pave for higher grounds as a chef.
You would better run fast, or you will not be able to catch up to me.
You look nice in that outfit.
I... I have to tell him!
Do not you think the yakisoba at night stands feel special?
It is different from the stuff you buy
in stores or the ones you have at home.
Yeah, I like the ones at night stands better.
Festivals are meant to deliver all wishes to the sky.
I felt like I have been running alone ever since you passed away.
I have a granddaughter who dreams to be like me.
If it were possible, just one more time...
I am going to be staying with my son.
So much time has passed, when I thought
I was just standing by the boiler.
I should probably be preparing to see the afterlife soon.
I do not plan on ever forgetting the precious memories
I thank all of you from the bottom of my heart.
I also thank you, Madam Manager.
It was a pleasure working with you.
Enjoy your stay with your grandchildren!
Mom, if you do not mind.
I want everyone to hear this.
I realize that I still have so much more to learn.
I cannot catch up to Mom, or even my sister.
We just were not born with the same level of talent, I guess.
I asked you guys to follow me,
but I am not capable of that yet.
Mom, I agree with you on shutting down the Kissuiso.
I do not want it to end forever.
I am going to study and train in order to reopen it someday.
Can I keep the name, Kissuiso?
I want to make an inn that will make you happy, Mom.
Young master, when that time comes,
I will be happy to lend you a hand.
I will leave my husband behind!
The dumber your kid is, the cuter, right?
Hey, you would better drink, too!
Do not stay too long, okay?
If you are going to do something,
be sure to write me a report afterwards.
Maybe I will go peek later.
I am going to be working at a friend's place for a little while.
Why do not you come to Tokyo with Ohana?
I plan on staying here and working as a waitress.
I am better at doing things myself
I will fest it up, too.
I will continue being that mother you hate so much, for your sake.
No, you have to fold back this part.
Sorry you had to be in this room,
I am actually feeling a bit guilty that I get to stay for free.
She was actually sort of happy because
she claims I never invite friends.
But you were right, this inn is really amazing.
Both the inn and the people who work here...
You found them all, did not you?
Watching you made me realize that places are not there to begin with.
You need to find them and build them yourself.
I will find my place, too.
If the places we belong happen to be the same,
Do not you think Ohana's boyfriend looks so sweet?
I feel so bad for Tohru that he lost to someone like that.
It is not about winning or losing!
Were not you going to sleep in the Madam Manager's room?
This is where I belong in the Kissuiso.
It is my first time ringing a bear-repelling bell!
I hear they often emerge during this season.
The convenience store is so far away.
The pajama party continues to the next day!
Oh, we forgot to buy meat buns...
I was wondering why it had to be the Kissuiso for me.
Well, maybe it is because you can be with Tohru.
Well, yeah, but that is not it!
I just wanted to become a chef.
Now, I want to become Kissuiso's chef.
I do not know about my dreams just yet, but...
I want to come back to the Kissuiso someday.
The place where many dreams are born.
We were there, were not we?
And we will be, in the future.
People agreed to preserve the Kissuiso as a
historical structure in the Yunosagi area.
I bid farewell to the time that passed by so quickly,
and at the same time, to the time that seemed so long.
I thought you would already left.
I sort of missed the train,
and there is some time left until the next one.
I wanted to thank the Kissuiso and say goodbye to it.
This wooden part right here looks like a face!
When I first came to the Kissuiso,
I thought it was like something out of a fairy tale.
And just as I would expected, a lot of crazy things happened.
So many things occurred in a day.
But that is because everyone was festing it up, was not it?
If a lot of people get together and fest it up,
it is only natural that many things happen.
What creates events are everyone is individual feelings.
It does not have to be here.
But still, I will return someday!
If you are going to come back someday,
keep these logs updated for Denroku's sake.
If you do not want it, then it is fine.
I am not giving it back!
I will write the rest for Beanman!
That is why, I will return...
I will be waiting for you.
Mom, it is time to get up!
Do not be late for your meeting!
I am probably still a bud.
But that is why, I stare up at the sun so high.
I quench my thirst with water.
I am a bud that is trying to bloom!
